PN,42206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1776856004
OL,3,CNHS trust removes advice to give
OL,4,Cchildren Wotsits, Skips and Cadbury
OL,5,CButtons
OL,7,FAccording to Gateshead Council's
OL,8,Fwebsite, under a section labelled
OL,9,F'Health inequalities for children,
OL,10,Fyoung people and families in
OL,11,FGateshead', it says the area has a
OL,12,Fhigher than average percentage of
OL,13,Fchildren in Reception who are
OL,14,Foverweight or obese.
OL,16,FThe percentage of children in
OL,17,FGateshead is 24%, while the England
OL,18,Faverage is 21.3%.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,423,420,120,260,000,100
PN,42207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F422A1776856004
OL,3,CNHS trust removes advice to give
OL,4,Cchildren Wotsits, Skips and Cadbury
OL,5,CButtons
OL,7,FThe trust spokesperson said its
OL,8,Fpriority was the safety and wellbeing
OL,9,Fof children and advised any parents or
OL,10,Fcarers with concerns about feeding or
OL,11,Fswallowing to contact their health
OL,12,Fvisitor, speech and language therapist
OL,13,For clinical team.
OL,15,F"We have removed the webpage while we
OL,16,Freview the wording to make sure it is
OL,17,Fclear and fully reflects current
OL,18,Fguidance and best practice," she
OL,19,Fadded. "We will publish updated
OL,20,Finformation once that review is
OL,21,Fcomplete."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
